"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"23c812",
"children":[
"Medications can produce almost any pattern of skin disease. The most common types of cutaneous adverse reactions are exanthematous/morbilliform, urticarial, fixed drug, and photosensitivity; drug-induced hypersensitivity syndrome; hypersensitivity vasculitis; acute generalized exanthematous pustulosis; and the severe cutaneous adverse reactions ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"Stevens-Johnson syndrome",
"children":[
"SJS"
]
},
" and toxic epidermal necrolysis."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s63_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"51ea97",
"children":[
"The appearance of a maculopapular rash is associated with the use of ampicillin in ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"Epstein-Barr virus",
"children":[
"EBV"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"cytomegalovirus",
"children":[
"CMV"
]
},
" infections or underlying ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"acute lymphoblastic leukemia",
"children":[
"ALL"
]
},
"."
]
},
" This is not a drug allergy. Duration of the rash is independent of whether the drug is continued."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"42173d",
"children":[
"The absence of eosinophilia does not rule out drug reaction or ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"drug reaction with eosinophilia and systemic symptoms",
"children":[
"DRESS"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s63_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"716a65",
"children":[
"Discontinue the offending medication, systemic and/or topical glucocorticoids, and oral ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"histamine type 1",
"children":[
"H",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"1"
]
}
]
},
" antihistamines as needed."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a05e18",
"children":[
"Treat drug-induced hypersensitivity syndrome with systemic glucocorticoids."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2f43f8",
"children":[
"SJS/",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"toxic epidermal necrolysis",
"children":[
"TEN"
]
},
" treatment is supportive (fluid and electrolyte management, wound care); the effectiveness of ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"intravenous immune globulin",
"children":[
"IVIG"
]
},
" and glucocorticoids is uncertain."
]
},
