"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"478857",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Acute generalized exanthematous pustulosis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fdef5e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Acute onset of widespread pustules, fever, leukocytosis, and possibly eosinophilia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e68d85",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Usually self-limiting and clears without residual skin changes approximately 2 weeks after drug cessation"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c809c2",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Drug-induced hypersensitivity syndrome (also known as DRESS)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"90f7c8",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Acute onset of generalized papular eruption, facial edema, fever, arthralgia, generalized lymphadenopathy, elevated serum aminotransferase levels, eosinophilia, and lymphocytosis"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-3 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"57a045",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"erythema multiforme",
"children":[
"EM"
]
},
","
]
},
" SJS, TEN"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2637ce",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Spectrum ranges from classic target lesions (EM), to involvement of mucous membranes with systemic symptoms (SJS), to a life-threatening loss of epidermis (TEN)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1f8a53",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"SJS involves <10%, SJS/TEN overlap involves 10%-30%, and TEN involves >30% skin detachment"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-4 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"663818",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Erythema nodosum"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"37a9ac",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Tender subcutaneous nodules on lower leg; often preceded by a prodrome of fever, malaise, and/or arthralgia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"272165",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Causes fall into three broad categories: infections, drugs, and systemic diseases (usually inflammatory disorders)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-5 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"93180f",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Fixed drug eruption"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e7a2a6",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Discrete, often round or oval lesions that recur in exactly the same spot when rechallenged with the drug"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-6 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f9bcec",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Maculopapular and morbilliform (small discrete papules)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"edfcbd",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Most common type of drug reaction; symmetric distribution, usually truncal, hardly ever on palms or soles, and associated with fever and pruritus"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-7 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8a53ae",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Red man syndrome"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f3d767",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Body flushing, hypotension, and muscle pain associated with vancomycin and ciprofloxacin"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-8 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
